{"key":"processedPost-18958198","value":{"id":18958198,"first":18957552,"last":18962442,"when":1381411689,"utime":"10/10/13 04:28 PM","content":"The problem is that <i>evaporation of moisture</i> is a major pinning trigger.&nbsp; Anything which slows down evaporation impedes this process.&nbsp; We get best results from an ebb and flow of substrate/casing moisture levels, and these crystals tend to cause a steady-state moisture level.&nbsp; That's good in plants, bad in mushroom growing.<br /><br />To obtain best performance in mushroom growing, we mist to hydrate the substrate or casing layer, and then let it start to dry out again before re-misting.<br />RR","title":"Re: Anyone used water crystals in sub or casing?"}}